**AgendaPro: Your Shopify for Beauty and Wellness in Latin America**

Founded in 2014 and backed by Y Combinator in Batch W21, AgendaPro is revolutionizing the beauty and wellness industry in Latin America. Based out of Santiago, Chile, this SaaS platform is designed specifically for businesses in the beauty and wellness sectors, making it easy for them to manage online payments and appointment scheduling seamlessly.

**Core Mission and Offering**
Imagine a world where beauty salons, medical clinics, and fitness studios can manage all their appointments and payments from one simple tool. That’s exactly what AgendaPro offers. By positioning itself as the “Shopify for Beauty and Wellness,” AgendaPro allows business owners to digitalize their scheduling processes, which includes features such as online booking, customer reminders, and integrated payment solutions. 

Their extensive client list includes over 20,000 businesses and manages more than 100 million appointments. The platform boasts impressive growth figures, with clients seeing sales increases of up to 82% after two years of usage.

**What Makes AgendaPro Stand Out?**
1. **All-in-One Management:** AgendaPro consolidates client management, appointment scheduling, payment processing, and customer marketing into a single platform.
2. **Customization:** Businesses can create personalized booking websites that reflect their branding and showcase their services.
3. **Flexible Functionality:** The software can be tailored to a variety of sectors within beauty and wellness—ranging from beauty salons to medical clinics.

**Functional Features**
- **Online Scheduling:** Simplifies the appointment booking process for both clients and service providers.
- **Automated Reminders:** Reduces no-show rates by sending reminders to clients ahead of their appointments.
- **Robust Reporting Tools:** Offers deep insights into business performance across various metrics, including client retention and sales.

**Support and Accessibility**
With a 50-strong team and ongoing support, clients are never left to navigate the system on their own. The platform also has a dedicated academy for users to learn best practices and maximize their use of AgendaPro’s features.

Quality customer service ensures that businesses can resolve issues in real-time, enhancing their overall experience on the platform.

**Conclusion**
In essence, AgendaPro is more than just a scheduling tool; it’s a comprehensive solution that empowers beauty and wellness businesses across Latin America to increase efficiency, improve customer satisfaction, and ultimately drive growth. Whether you run a cozy hair salon or a bustling clinic, AgendaPro equips you with the tools to thrive in a competitive marketplace. 

For more information, check their website [here](https://www.agendapro.com).

description:
We build tools that allows enterprises verify information about a user *before* processing it - whether it is processed by a human or an AI agent.

Traditionally, these verifications including but not limited to background checks cost ~$10. Using our advancements in AI and Cryptography, we're able to send that cost to a few cents. 

This enables enterprises to do verification at scale, earlier in their work-flows, and enables new kinds of businesses - which were not performing these verifications because of prohibitively high costs.

For example, it makes no sense that a recruiter does a candidate's document verification and background checks AFTER the candidate has cleared all the interviews. That's because that verification is cumbersome and expensive. They can't afford to verify all the candidates at the top of the funnel. Many such workflows are ripe for disruption. 

Another example of a product that was not possible before. A dating app uses our tools to verify the users' information - including their employment, education and financial background. This was something that would have been too expensive to verify at a $10 pricepoint where the ARPU is only $8. 

Not only that, we're designing the tools ground up - so that AI agents can utilize these verifications before ingesting information, so that they take action basis truthful information.

We have 3 tools
1. BlueCheck : our flagship product for background verification. The cheapest option to verify users' employment, education and financial background. A few cents instead of a few tens of dollars. Several Billion Dollar+ revenue companies are customers. A solution designed for enterprises that works out of the box!
2. Reclaim Protocol : our underlying infrastructure that makes BlueCheck possible. With advancements in cryptography, specifically zero knowledge proofs - our research over the last 3 years have resulted in inventing a new cryptographic primitive called zkTLS, which allows us to verify information from any website using the cryptography of the existing internet pipes (TLS). This is our secret sauce!
3. Questbook : our dog-fooding tool. Questbook is a tool to give out research and open source software development grants. These grants are reviewed by AI agents that we built inhouse. The biggest scam people try is to fake who they are when they are applying for grants. We dog-food our own tools to make sure we verify all the claims the users are making when they apply for grants. Our tools secure more than $10M of grants being given out on the platform. So it's high stakes, and it works!

description:
In a nutshell: many diseases are caused by how much your cells squeeze (asthma, fibrosis, others). We discover drugs that control how much cells squeeze, with ease, to treat disease.

We use patented bioMEMS technology to turn cell strength (cells' ability to pull/ squeeze) into a quantifiable metric in drug discovery, to help find better drugs for mechanical diseases. 

We screen 100,000s of drugs against numerous contractile human cell types to comprehensively map human mechanobiology (the "contractome") and identify promising drug development starting points to deliver novel medicines to treat mechanically-driven diseases including asthma, hypertension, preterm labor, fibrosis, and others.

**Founded:** 2020

---

**Mission Statement:**  
Lunatic is dedicated to creating powerful operating systems specifically designed for server-side applications.

---

**What is Lunatic?**  
At its core, Lunatic is a WebAssembly runtime inspired by Erlang, aimed at building low-latency, robust, and distributed networking applications. Think gaming servers, web apps, or video chat platforms—anything that needs speed and reliability. By leveraging WebAssembly, Lunatic allows developers to use existing codebases and libraries from various programming languages, making it an attractive option for teams looking to enhance their projects.

---

**Key Features:**

- **Open Source:** Built under a dual Apache/MIT license, fostering collaboration and community contributions.
  
- **Performance:** Utilizes JIT-compiled WebAssembly for high-throughput and low-latency services.

- **Security:** Each process runs in a sandboxed environment, minimizing risks associated with untrusted code.

- **Fault Tolerance:** Monitors processes through supervision trees, inspired by Erlang to ensure system resilience.

- **Portability:** Compile once and run anywhere—supporting different architectures and operating systems.

- **Distributed Capabilities:** Nodes can easily connect via QUIC with mTLS authentication, allowing for seamless scaling.

---

**Ideal Use Cases:**  
Lunatic shines in scenarios that require massive concurrency and high fault tolerance, making it suitable for real-time systems where reliability is non-negotiable. Whether you're working with traditional web applications or modern gaming services, Lunatic provides the robust foundation you need.

Recover provides more effective and affordable addiction treatment via telemedicine. We partner with local governments to save lives and taxpayer dollars.

More than 20 million Americans struggle with addiction, but less than 10% of people who need it receive treatment. For those that do, it usually does not work - only 8% get better. Most of this treatment is funded by governments, and goes to programs that are frequently predatory, and focus more on profit than people.

We have created an effective, accessible, and affordable solution: Recover. We offer a proven approach using medication and counseling, that can improve outcomes for over 70% of patients. It reduces overdoses by 80%, death by 50%, and has years of research and application showing it works. 

Despite how effective this medication can be, most rehabs do not have medical professionals on staff. Not only does our program work better and bring medicine to addiction care, it also costs just 10% of traditional programs.

Nick founded Recover after seeing his family and friends struggle with addiction. He was raised by a drug addict, has an alcoholic brother, and lost an uncle to heroin. He saw how hard it is for people to get the treatment they need, and how ineffective existing options are. We are working to make sure that people like Nick’s family have access to best-in-class addiction treatment so they can get and stay well.

description:
REGENT is building a new mode of transportation that will redefine regional mobility by mid-decade. Their first product, the seaglider, is an all-electric, hydrofoiling boat-plane that operates within a wingspan of the water's surface.  By flying low on a cushion of air, seagliders unlock the ability to fly twice as far as an electric aircraft, while being regulated by maritime authorities enabling market entry for a fraction of the cost.

REGENT has de-risked seaglider technology with a ¼-scale, 400 lb, flying demonstration vehicle and a full-scale wing test section. By 2024, REGENT will fly humans on the first full-scale prototype seaglider.  By mid-decade, REGENT’s customers - airlines and ferry companies – will begin commercial seaglider service on the 12-seat initial product.

In just two years, REGENT has accumulated $8B in provisional orders (including firm deposits) proving the potential of the $25B+ initial market. 

REGENT, a team of 40, is led by MIT-trained, ex-Boeing engineers Billy Thalheimer and Mike Klinker.  REGENT has raised $50M to date from the likes of Thiel Capital, Founders Fund, Mark Cuban, Y Combinator, and includes strategic investment from Japan Airlines, Hawaiian Airlines and Mesa Airlines.

Founded in 2020 and based in Detroit, MI, Remora is tackling carbon emissions from semi-trucks head-on. Imagine a device that not only captures CO2 directly from a truck's tailpipe but also turns this environmental effort into a profit opportunity for truck operators.

**Mission:**
Remora’s goal is straightforward—reduce emissions from heavy-duty trucks while generating revenue. They achieve this through a patented device that filters carbon from exhaust gases, giving trucking companies a new income stream by selling the captured CO2 or using it to earn carbon credits.

**How It Works:**
1. **Installation:** The device is designed to easily bolt onto Class 8 trucks without making permanent modifications.

**Business Model:**

### Serna Bio: Unlocking the Potential of RNA Therapeutics

**Overview:**
Founded in 2021 and hailing from the Y Combinator Batch W21, Serna Bio is making waves in the biotech landscape. Located in Ontario, CA, this innovative company consists of a skilled team of nine, dedicated to harnessing the power of genetic medicine through small molecules.

**Mission:**
At its core, Serna Bio aims to revolutionize genetic medicine by developing small molecules aimed at modulating RNA function. This pioneering approach targets diseases that have traditionally resisted treatment by focusing on the transcriptome—the part of the genome that encodes RNA. While only 2% of the human genome produces proteins, a staggering 70% is dedicated to RNA, which poses vast and largely untapped potential for drug discovery.

**What They Do:**
Serna Bio operates at the cutting-edge intersection of synthetic biology, machine learning (ML), and high-throughput screening. The company’s research and development efforts center on:

1. **Mapping RNA Architecture**: By creating a detailed map of functional RNA structures, they identify druggable RNA motifs across the transcriptome.
2. **Developing Small Molecules**: These molecules modulate translation and splicing processes to create therapeutics for challenging, high-unmet medical need targets.
3. **Utilizing AI**: The company has built the world’s largest database of functional RNA structures combined with unique chemical libraries, driving both internal research and external collaborations.

**Current Projects:**
Serna Bio’s unique approach involves cutting-edge in vitro assays and machine learning technologies. By combining these tools, they've uncovered a deeper understanding of how RNA works, allowing them to innovate in the realm of RNA-targeted therapies. 

If you're intrigued by the confluence of biology and technology, and the promise of RNA as a therapeutic target, Serna Bio is paving the way forward.

**Get in Touch:**
The team at Serna Bio welcomes collaboration and new talent to push the boundaries of RNA therapeutics even further. For inquiries or opportunities, you can reach out via their [website](http://serna.bio).

**In Conclusion:**
Serna Bio is boldly pushing the frontiers of drug discovery by reimagining RNA's role in genetic medicine. With an innovative focus and robust scientific foundation, they stand at the precipice of potentially transformative breakthroughs in how we treat a range of diseases.

Snazzy's mission is straightforward: democratize access to clear aligner treatment in India. By leveraging cutting-edge teledentistry, the company is offering high-quality aligners at a fraction of the typical costs seen in the market.

- **Expert Guidance**: Constant monitoring and support from dental professionals.
- **Smile Guarantee**: If further adjustments are needed, Snazzy covers the cost of new aligners.
- **Convenience**: Removable aligners mean no dietary restrictions—eat what you love without worry!

### SoloSuit: Empowering Consumers in Legal Disputes

**Introduction**  
SoloSuit is on a mission to turn everyday people into superhumans by equipping them with the necessary tools to win disputes. Founded in 2018 and a proud member of Y Combinator's W21 batch, SoloSuit takes on the daunting world of debt collection lawsuits, aiming to disrupt the $3.5 billion consumer litigation market.

**Headquarters and Team**  
Situated in Provo, Utah, SoloSuit operates with a tight-knit team of six employees. At the helm is Group Partner Dalton Caldwell, guiding the vision of this innovative legal tech company.

**What They Do**  
Originally branded just as SoloSuit, the company provides services that demystify the process of resolving debt disputes. Their primary offerings include:

- **Debt Answer**: This service helps individuals respond to debt lawsuits efficiently. SoloSuit prepares a legal response, gets it reviewed by an attorney, and files it on behalf of the consumer within the critical 14-30 day window after receiving a complaint.
  
- **SoloSettle**: An alternative that focuses on negotiating settlements outside of court. It helps users settle debts for less than the owed amount, which can be a realistic and less stressful solution compared to litigation.

**Impressive Reach**  
Since its inception, SoloSuit has made significant strides. The company reports having protected $1.8 billion worth of debt and assisting over 274,000 people across all 50 states. 

**Recognition**  
SoloSuit has garnered attention from major media outlets, including NPR, TechCrunch, and Bloomberg, recognizing its innovative approach to a traditionally intimidating area of consumer law. 

**Conclusion**  
In a landscape where debt collection can easily feel overwhelming, SoloSuit stands out as a beacon of empowerment, enabling individuals to take control of their financial disputes with confidence. For anyone facing debt lawsuits or looking to settle debts, SoloSuit is more than just a service—it's a partner in achieving a fair resolution.

To learn more, visit [SoloSuit.com](https://www.solosuit.com).

**SpruceID Overview: Mastering Digital Identity Control**

Founded in 2020 and part of Y Combinator's W21 batch, SpruceID is based in New York and has quickly gathered a talented team of 25. Their mission? To empower individuals to take control of their personal data across the web. Think of it as shifting the power dynamic: instead of users logging into various platforms, platforms should gain access to their data vaults. This twist on digital identity positions SpruceID not just as a product but as a critical building block for a free society in the digital age.

### What They Do 

SpruceID's offerings include a suite of products designed for the issuance and verification of digital credentials. Their flagship product, **Credible**, is a robust end-to-end solution for verifiable identities—think of digital driver's licenses and other necessary credentials in our increasingly digital world. They also provide **SpruceKit**, an open-source library to help developers integrate these capabilities into their applications.

#### Key Solutions:
- **Issuance**: Digital IDs, passes, permits, and supply chain credentials.
- **Verification**: Secure methods for online and in-person checks of digital credentials.

### Industry Reach

SpruceID isn’t just targeting a single market; their solutions are applicable across several sectors including government, healthcare, education, financial services, marketplaces, and the emerging Web3 space. This versatility not only broadens their impact but also reinforces the importance of privacy and individual autonomy in those domains.

### The Foundation of Their Mission

At SpruceID, privacy-by-design is not just a buzzword—it's embedded in their architecture. They believe in creating frameworks that enhance individual autonomy, a necessity for fostering dynamic economies and vibrant, free societies. Their journey has led them to partner with notable organizations, including the California DMV for mobile driver's licenses, showcasing their expertise in crafting secure and user-friendly digital identities.

### The Big Picture

As we navigate an age where AI can easily generate fake identities, SpruceID addresses the looming identity crisis head-on. Their techniques and security features are designed to withstand these challenges, ensuring genuine interactions in the digital realm.

In essence, SpruceID is redefining how we perceive and handle digital identity. Their vision transcends mere technology; it's about ensuring that people retain control over their identities, a principle that resonates deeply in today’s fast-evolving digital landscape.

For more information, visit their website at [SpruceID.com](https://www.spruceid.com).

### Trestle Biotherapeutics: Pioneering Bioengineered Solutions for Kidney Health

Founded in 2020 and part of Y Combinator's Winter 2021 batch, Trestle Biotherapeutics is on a mission to transform the lives of patients suffering from kidney failure. Based in San Diego, CA, this biotech startup is small but mighty, with a lean team of just two employees. This focused team is driven by a powerful vision: to develop bioengineered kidneys that could alleviate the burdens of dialysis and extend the time patients can avoid transplantation.

#### The Problem They're Tackling

Kidney disease is a pressing global health issue, impacting around 850 million people worldwide, including 37 million in the United States. For those who progress to end-stage renal disease (ESRD), treatment options are limited to kidney transplants or dialysis—both of which come with significant limitations and risks. Dialysis, while lifesaving, can be a grueling process and doesn't advance treatment options despite its long history.

#### Trestle's Innovative Approach

Trestle is developing a novel implantable therapeutic tissue that aims to supplement kidney function upon surgical delivery. This innovative solution could not only help patients transition off dialysis but also buy them time before the need for a kidney transplant arises. Essentially, they're working towards creating a bioengineered organ that could one day serve as a replacement for traditional kidney transplants.

"We see our work as not just a solution for a problem but a catalyst to bridge various scientific disciplines, leading to breakthroughs not just for kidney disease, but potentially for other organ failures too," says co-founders Ben Shepherd, PhD, and Alice Chen, PhD.

### The Team Behind Trestle

- **Ben Shepherd, PhD**: Co-Founder and CEO. With over a decade of experience in tissue engineering and vascular biology, Ben previously held leadership roles in research and development at Organovo, focusing on complex 3D human tissue systems.
  
- **Alice Chen, PhD**: Co-Founder and Chief Scientific Officer. Renowned for her expertise in stem cell biology and bioprinting, Alice has a rich history in early-stage biotech, previously directing R&D pipeline development at Organovo.

Their combined experience and knowledge in biofabrication, fluidics, and stem cell biology equip Trestle with the necessary tools to tackle this complex challenge.

### Milestones and Recognition

Trestle has garnered significant traction in the biotech community, recently winning a $1 million prize from the KidneyX Innovation Accelerator through the Artificial Kidney Prize program. This recognition is a testament to their innovative approach and the potential of their technology to address urgent healthcare needs.

They have also joined the Wellcome Leap HOPE program, aligning with other forward-thinking organizations to accelerate their research and development efforts.

### Why "Trestle"?

The name "Trestle" symbolizes a bridge—connecting patients to better health solutions and bridging various scientific disciplines. It's about fostering collaboration across the globe to create solutions that can change lives. The company embodies an ambitious and multifaceted approach to bioengineering, blending academic rigor with entrepreneurial spirit.

### Future Aspirations

Trestle Biotherapeutics aims to disrupt the treatment landscape for kidney failure, and if they succeed, the impact could ripple through multiple fields, providing a new paradigm in organ replacement therapies. By harnessing cutting-edge technologies and a collaborative spirit, Trestle hopes to turn its vision into reality and ultimately serve millions of patients in need. 

For more information, visit [Trestle Biotherapeutics](http://www.trestlebio.com).
headline: Bioengineered kidneys for patients with kidney failure
name: Trestle Biotherapeutics

### Udhaar App: Revolutionizing Finances for SMEs in Pakistan

**Introduction**  
Founded in 2020 and part of Y Combinator’s W21 batch, Udhaar App is on a mission to become the **Khatabook** and **OkCredit** of Pakistan. With a simple yet powerful bookkeeping solution, the company aims to help around **30 million** micro and small enterprises (SMEs) take their financial operations digital.

**The Spark that Ignited Udhaar**  
The concept for Udhaar App emerged during a trip to Pakistan when a local store owner shared his struggles—working **16 hours a day, seven days a week** just to combat theft and manage finances manually. This precarious balance between work and family inspired the founders to find ways to enable small business owners to run their operations more efficiently, giving them time back to enjoy life.

**Understanding the Landscape**  
Pakistan's business environment has traditionally relied on manual bookkeeping for everything—store credit, sales tracking, cash management, and tax filings. This outdated system needed change, and Udhaar App stepped up to fill that gap. With SMEs contributing **74% to the overall GDP**, their potential for growth is enormous.

**Growth & Technology Adoption**  
In the backdrop of exploding 4G adoption—**91 million subscribers** and a **720% growth** in five years—product-market fit has accelerated, evidenced by: 
- Over **1 million downloads**
- An impressive **4.6-star rating** on both the Play Store and App Store

**What Udhaar Offers**  
Udhaar App is essentially an all-in-one platform tailored to the distinct needs of small businesses. Here’s a peek into the features:

1. **Udhaar Book** - Manage credit and payments with ease.
2. **Cash Book** - Track cash flow and business expenses.
3. **Staff Book** - Automate payroll and attendance.
4. **Stock Book** - Keep inventory in check with alerts for low stock.
5. **Invoice Book & Sale POS** - Simplifies invoicing and point of sale.

Beyond bookkeeping, it also acts as a payment processor, enabling businesses to collect payments swiftly and securely.

**Community Trust & Usage**  
With over **5.1 million businesses** already using Udhaar App to efficiently manage their finances, it’s becoming a vital tool in the entrepreneurial ecosystem of Pakistan. The company’s ambition is to empower these businesses not just to survive, but thrive.

**Conclusion**  
Udhaar App embodies an intersection of technology and financial freedom in Pakistan. The founders are on to something big, addressing a vital need in the marketplace while tapping into the vast potential of SMEs. If you’re in Pakistan and running a small business, this could be the app that liberates you from the manual grind, allowing you to focus on what’s truly important—growing your business and spending time with your family.

For more information, visit their website [Udhaar App](https://udhaar.pk/).
headline: We're Khatabook / OkCredit for Pakistan

**Valink Therapeutics: Innovating Cancer Treatment with Bispecific Antibody Drug Conjugates**

Founded in 2021 as part of Y Combinator's Batch W21, Valink Therapeutics is a Boston-based biotech company focused on transforming cancer treatment through the development of bispecific antibody drug conjugates (bsADCs). Their mission is to discover more effective drugs targeted at solid tumors, areas of cancer biology that have been poorly addressed by existing immunotherapies.

### What's Special About Valink?

Valink operates on a cutting-edge technology platform, LiliumX™, which allows for rapid design and testing of novel drug candidates. Unlike traditional methods that can take months to generate potential treatments, Valink's approach can produce thousands of drug candidates within days by incorporating multiple modifications to antibodies at once. This multitasking capability enhances their ability to create complex drug candidates that feature bi- and multispecificity, multivalency, and drug-conjugation—all in one streamlined process.

### The Science Behind the Solutions

The bsADCs developed by Valink use a dual-targeting mechanism, enabling improved efficacy by more precisely delivering therapeutic payloads to malignant tissues while sparing healthy cells. This is particularly important in treating solid tumors where distinguishing between cancerous and healthy cells can be a significant challenge. By targeting two markers simultaneously, Valink's drugs hold the promise of being not just more effective but also safer.

### The Team and Investors

With a compact team of 14 employees, Valink leverages the expertise and resources from prestigious backers, including RV Invest, Hoxton Ventures, and others, underscoring confidence in their innovative approach to drug discovery.

### The Road Ahead

Valink Therapeutics is on a mission to unlock unprecedented therapies that will change the game in oncology. As they continue their work, we can look forward to new developments that could significantly improve outcomes for patients battling cancer.

For more details, visit their [website](https://www.valinktx.com/).
headline: Discovering bispecific antibody drug-conjugates (BsADC) against cancer
name: Valink Therapeutics

generated_description:
### Wasp: Building Enterprise Apps at Lightning Speed

**Overview of Wasp**

Founded in 2020 and part of Y Combinator's W21 batch, Wasp is a developer-focused company based in Zagreb, Croatia. Their mission? To enable developers to create sophisticated enterprise web applications **10 times faster** than traditional methods. By minimizing boilerplate and providing a simple configuration language, Wasp allows developers to focus on writing the essential code while leveraging tools like React, Node.js, and Prisma. Think of it as a Rails-like framework for modern web apps.

**The Problem Wasp Solves**

Developers often face the daunting task of mastering several technologies to build a web app, which can be frustrating and time-consuming. Wasp elegantly bridges this gap, offering a streamlined approach to application development. With Wasp, you don’t need to juggle multiple technologies; rather, you can write your app using a single `.wasp` file that clearly outlines your app’s structure and functionality.

**What Makes Wasp Unique?**

1. **Configuration Language**: Wasp employs a simple configuration syntax, allowing developers to define their application's core components without delving into excessive coding.
   
2. **Full-stack Framework**: It combines the power of popular frameworks like React for the frontend and Node.js for the backend while managing the complexities of deployment with ease.

3. **Open Source**: Wasp is fully open-source, encouraging developers to contribute and collaborate on enhancing its features. This accessibility and community-driven approach foster innovation.

4. **Type Safety**: It integrates seamlessly with TypeScript, ensuring type safety throughout your application. This means fewer runtime errors, leading to more robust applications.

5. **Rapid Development**: Developers can launch an entire app in just a day and make production deployments with a single command using a straightforward CLI.

**Current Features**

Wasp supports a plethora of functionalities that simplify the development lifecycle:

- **Authentication**: Built-in full-stack authentication options with various methods (Google, GitHub, email).
- **Data Management**: A typesafe RPC layer that connects client-server logic directly, eliminating tedious backend calls.
- **Job Scheduling**: Tools for defining and running scheduled tasks on the server.
- **Custom Deployments**: Wasp's CLI helpers guide users through deploying applications to popular platforms.

**The Road Ahead**

Wasp is continually evolving, with a solid roadmap that includes improvements like expanding Prisma support, introducing more social authentication options, and adding support for server-side rendering (SSR). The founders are laser-focused on making Wasp an invaluable tool for developers.

**Community and Resources**

You can find even more about Wasp through their [website](https://wasp-lang.dev/), or join their community on [Discord](https://wasp-lang.dev/</discord>) to connect with fellow developers. The platform has garnered attention for its ease of use—some users have managed to launch full-stack applications over a weekend!

**In Conclusion**

Wasp isn't just another development tool; it's a game changer for enterprise application development. By simplifying the process and providing robust capabilities, it allows developers to turn ideas into reality faster than ever. If you’re looking to build quickly while maintaining best practices, Wasp is definitely worth a look.
headline: Configuration language for building enterprise web apps 10x faster
name: Wasp

- **Headless CMS**: A GraphQL-based solution that serves as the backbone for managing content.

- **Multi-Tenancy**: Allows for the management of multiple projects from a single instance, perfect for enterprise solutions.

If you're navigating the complexities of serverless development and need a robust, customizable platform that emphasizes data ownership and security, Webiny is worth exploring. description:
Wyndly (https://www.wyndly.com) fixes allergies by training patients' bodies to ignore their allergy triggers. Frustrated allergy suffers come to us when they no longer want to deal with pills and sprays. We diagnose the patient’s unique allergy profile and create a personalized treatment plan to give the patient lifelong allergy relief. Specifically, Wyndly is increasing access to  sublingual immunotherapy (SLIT) for allergy care. For our patients, we're combining the convenience of telehealth and direct-to-consumer care with an exceptional patient experience that never loses the context of care.

Wyndly represents an opportunity to change allergy care forever. With 60 million Americans suffering from allergies today, and with this number doubling over the coming years, there's simply an incredible need for the convenient care Wyndly provides. 

You can read more about us in [Techcrunch](https://techcrunch.com/2021/02/12/wyndly-aims-to-bring-allergy-drops-to-the-masses/).

The Wyndly Model 

At Wyndly, we believe that better connections lead to better care, and we’re committed to making both happen at every step of the patient journey. Our allergy practice allows our patients to work with expert providers to develop personalized treatment plans for long-term allergy relief using clinically proven therapies. From a patient’s initial consultation to their final treatment delivery, we want the Wyndly experience to be a breath of fresh air for allergy sufferers – truly effective allergy relief, simply and efficiently delivered.

Once we've conquered allergies, we're transforming the care model for every chronic condition. While transactional care for purchasing pills has flourished in telehealth, no one has gone after chronic care. Patients with chronic conditions are shuffled between providers, insurance, and more -- and they never feel heard. These patients deserve better, and we're going to give it to them. Wyndly is starting with allergies, but we'll expand into asthma, sleep apnea, and other conditions in the near future.

Our values

**Compassion**: We approach all our patients and partners with an open mind and a genuine desire to be of service.

description:
Zealth is building remote monitoring software to help hospitals provide automated continuous round-the-clock support to their cancer patients post-discharge. 

Hospitals are overburdened with no resources to provide care to their chronic patients once they leave the hospital. For instance, in India, there are only 2200 oncologists for 1.38 billion people. Patients travel 100 miles waiting for hours to get few minutes with the doctors. They have no easy means to manage all the toxicities and symptoms they get once they are back home. This leads to 6X lower patient retention, 4X high emergency readmissions, and poor patient outcomes. 

Zealth bridges this gap through its digital health intervention platform.

### Zealth: Transforming Cancer Patient Monitoring

**Overview**  
Founded in 2020 and part of Y Combinator's W21 batch, Zealth operates out of Bengaluru, India, with a nimble team of just two employees. Its mission? To provide software for the remote monitoring of cancer patients, making post-hospital care more accessible and effective.

**The Need**  
The statistics are stark: In India, with a staggering population of 1.38 billion, there are only 2,200 oncologists available. Patients often journey over 100 miles to secure mere minutes of a doctor's time, leading to 6 times lower patient retention and 4 times higher emergency readmissions. The post-treatment phase for cancer patients is chaotic—symptoms and toxicities abound, often leaving patients in confusion without accessible help.

**The Solution**  
Zealth's platform aims to bridge this gap. By leveraging machine learning, it offers an end-to-end solution for real-time health monitoring and symptom management for cancer patients at home. The software alerts patients when it's time to reach out to their doctors and provides actionable insights tailored for clinicians. This not only enhances patient engagement but significantly lightens the load on healthcare providers, allowing them to focus on what they do best—care for their patients.

**What They Do**  
1. **Patients**: Empower them to track symptoms and receive real-time alerts.
2. **Clinicians**: Provide a 360-degree view of their patients' statuses from home, simplifying follow-ups and decision-making.
3. **Insurers**: Help reduce claims through proactive health interventions.
4. **Clinical Trials**: Generate real-world evidence that can streamline clinical trials while driving down costs.

**Impact**  
The feedback from users highlights the platform's efficacy:
- Caregivers appreciate the symptom-tracking capabilities, which help save time and enhance peace of mind.
- Doctors report improved patient follow-up and engagement thanks to the tools provided by Zealth.

**Conclusion**  
With the pressing need for efficient post-discharge monitoring of cancer patients, Zealth is tackling a critical healthcare challenge head-on. They provide not just a service, but a lifeline that empowers patients and eases the burdens on the healthcare system.

For more information, you can visit their website at [Zealth](https://zealth-ai.com).
headline: Software for remote monitoring of cancer patients
